[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626839&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626839&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

You have to get the NIC (or whomever) to delegate you the IN-ADDR.ARPA
domains for the networks you manage just as you get a namespace domain
or domains to name your hosts in.  If you just set up the zones in your
server without registering with the NIC, address to name queries may
work locally, but the outside world does not know how to get to the
servers which can map addresses in this particular network back into
names.

paul

